## 3. Summary

The implemented PID controller incorporates essential real-world considerations:

* Anti-windup prevents instability during actuator saturation
* Derivative filtering ensures robustness against sensor noise
* A structured tuning protocol enables safe deployment on physical systems

These design choices are critical for reliable and safe operation in practical robotic applications, particularly in systems with mechanical constraints such as backlash and hard-stops.
